    "122787063": {
      "title": "Classical orthogonal polynomials: Dependence of parameters",
      "abstract": "Most of the classical orthogonal polynomials (continuous, discrete and their q-analogues) can be considered as functions of several parameters ci. A systematic study of the variation, innitesimal and nite, of these polynomials Pn(x;ci) with respect to the parameters ci is proposed. A method to get recurrence relations for connection coecients linking (@ r =@c r i)Pn(x;ci )t oPn(x;ci) is given and, in some situations, explicit expressions are obtained. This allows us to compute new integrals or sums of classical orthogonal polynomials using the digamma function. A basic theorem on the zeros of (@=@ci)Pn(x;ci) is also proved. c 2000 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved. MSC: 33C25; 42C05; 33B15"
    }
